entries.femaleVariant: She was right.
Fuck, V!
You just stood there and watched her play us?
Decided to give her a chance.
Change should come gradually.
She was right, Judy. Granted, didn't tell us what she was plannin', but she prolly knew you wouldn't agree to it.
Decided to give her a chance. Figured you had a reason to take this to her.
Changes this big need to come gradually. Revolution always sounds great in theory.
Fine... Augh, I'm sorry. Got carried away, I... Just, this ain't how I imagined things panning out.
It's OK, I get it.
Evelyn also wanted everything in one go.
Your frustration, I get it.
Don't take this personally, but I gotta cool down.
Evelyn wanted everything in one go too, and... heh, immediately.
entries.maleVariant: Evelyn wanted everything in one go too, and uh, heh... immediately.

entries.femaleVariant: That's true.
Gonna go.
Thanks for the help, V. Thank you, again.
I'm sorry.
Wasn't my fault.
Sorry, Judy. I-I didn't plan for it to happen.
entries.maleVariant: I'm sorry, Judy, I... I didn't plan for it to happen.

entries.femaleVariant: I know.
Wouldn't've happened if she hadn't come at me. Wasn't my fault.
Eh, sorry, but... I don't buy that. Could've found another way.
You... Y-you killed her?!
Fuck... Should've seen that comin'.
Clouds is free, that's what's important.
There's a difference between being a gonk and having faith in people.
Who cares that she was schemin'? We did it, that's what matters. Clouds belongs to the dolls now.
entries.maleVariant: Who cares that she was schemin'? Heh, we did it, that's what matters. Clouds belongs to the dolls now.

entries.femaleVariant: You're right. That was the plan all along.
Don't be dramatic, Judy. There's a difference between bein' a gonk and believin' people wanna do good.
entries.maleVariant: Ah, don't be dramatic, Judy. There's a difference between bein' a gonk and believin' people wanna do good.

entries.femaleVariant: I know you do. Don't need to believe that. I just know it.
Least you had the decency not to take her eddies.
As if that wasn't enough, you took her eddies, too.
Bullshit! You're just spewing words now, V.
You took her eddies, so the sich is clear, cut and dried for me.
Thank you.
Thank you.
Didn't want a bloodbath.
If I hadn't settled it quietly, Hiromi wouldn't've been the last casualty.
She would've been worse than Hiromi.
Given what I saw, I knew she'd be a bigger jackbooted tyrant than Hiromi.
And that was reason enough to take her life?
O-oh my fucking god... You killed her.
Maybe you're right. I'm sorry.
She should've been aware of the consequences.
Maybe you're right. I-I let her get to me. Sorry things ended this way.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, maybe you're right. I let her get to me. I'm sorry things ended this way.

entries.femaleVariant: So am I.
Maiko knew what she was starting, what she was doing. She knew it could all come crashing down.
Thought she was untouchable all her life…
Well... not my fault she was wrong.
entries.maleVariant: Well... it's not my fault she was wrong.

entries.femaleVariant: Probably had this planned from the start – same sec we walked into her office.
Jesus, am I a gonk.
And you made it happen.
Well fuck!
Club as big as this, operating in such a niche, needs a strong hand at the helm.
entries.maleVariant: A club as big as this, operating in such a niche, needs a strong hand at the helm.

entries.femaleVariant: Seeing as you trusted her, why should I have doubted her?
entries.maleVariant: Seein' as you trusted her, why should I have doubted her?

entries.femaleVariant: Don't pin this on me.
I'm not. She knows the harsh realities at Clouds better than I do... Better than you do, even.
entries.maleVariant: I'm not. She knows the harsh realities at Clouds better'n I do... Better'n you, even.

entries.femaleVariant: But Night City's about wheelin' and dealin'.
That's where you and I differ. For you, it's about profit. For me, it's about the people.
You're a merc. She's a soulless, conniving bitch, and I'm a sorry-ass gonk.
First casualties of revolution – revolutionaries. Bring anarchy to Clouds and it'd go to shit. Everybody'd wind up in the street.
entries.maleVariant: First casualties of revolution – revolutionaries. Bring anarchy to Clouds and it'd go to shit. Everybody'd wind up on the street.

entries.femaleVariant: How many lives would you be willin' to sacrifice for your pipe dream?
But... guess I should get used to it... Heh, no matter what you do, life's always gonna throw you a curveball.
And a strong gang to back it up.
I'd always tell her that.
Just, gimme a sec. Gotta gather my wits.
I, uh... I gotta process all this. In peace. Alone.
Be seein' ya, V.
See you later, V.
[Step away] See ya, Judy.
Well, then... see ya, Judy.
[Step away] No problem. See ya.
Don't mention it. See ya around, Judy.
[Step away] See ya.
See ya, Judy.
[Step away] Take care, Judy.
See you around, Judy.
